{{About|the anthropologist|the poet|Kate Fox (writer)}}
{{Use British English|date=January 2013}}
'''Kate Fox''' is a [[Social anthropology|social anthropologist]], co-director of the [[Social Issues Research Centre]] (SIRC)<ref>{{cite news|title=Kate Fox: Behaviour sleuth|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/kate-fox-behaviour-sleuth-502278.html|work=Independent | location=London}}</ref> and a Fellow of the Institute for Cultural Research.<ref>{{cite web|title=Fellows / Dr Kate Fox | publisher=Institute for Cultural Research|url=http://www.i-c-r.org.uk/fellows.php | accessdate=13 January 2014}}</ref> She has written several books, including ''[[Watching the English|Watching the English: The Hidden Rules of English Behaviour]]''.

==Background==
Kate Fox is the daughter of [[Anthropology|anthropologist]] [[Robin Fox]].  As a child she lived in the UK, the [[United States]], [[France]], and [[Ireland]]. She studied for an undergraduate degree in [[anthropology]] and [[philosophy]] at [[Cambridge University]]. In 1989 she became co-director of [[MCM Research|MCM Research Ltd.]], and continues to provide consulting services.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kate Fox bio at MCM Research|url=http://www.mcmresearch.co.uk/kate.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130121175854/http://www.mcmresearch.co.uk/kate.html | archivedate=21 January 2013 | publisher=MCM Research|accessdate=13 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=About MCM Research|url=http://www.mcmresearch.co.uk/about.html|publisher=MCM Research|accessdate=11 February 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110907010015/http://www.mcmresearch.co.uk/about.html|archivedate=7 September 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref>  She is now a co-director of the [[Social Issues Research Centre]], based in [[Oxford, England]].<ref name="SIRC_bio">{{cite web|url=http://www.sirc.org/about/kate_fox.html|title=SIRC bio of Kate Fox}}</ref>

==Publications==
Fox has written a number of books. Her titles include:

*{{cite book |last=Marsh|first=Peter |title=Drinking and Public Disorder: A Report of Research Conducted for the Portman Group by MCM Research |year=1992 |publisher=Portman Group|isbn=978-0-9518762-0-6|author2=Kate Fox Kibby}}
*{{cite book |author=Kate Fox |title=Pubwatching with Desmond Morris |year=1993 |publisher=Alan Sutton |isbn=978-0-7509-0532-9}}
*{{cite book |author=Kate Fox |url=http://www.sirc.org/publik/ptpintro.html |title=Passport to the Pub: The Tourist's Guide to Pub Etiquette |year=1996 |publisher=Brewers and Licensed Retailers Association |isbn=978-1-899344-09-3}}
*{{cite book |author=Kate Fox |title=The Racing Tribe: Watching the Horsewatchers |date=7 Oct 1999 |publisher=Metro Books |isbn=978-0-7658-0838-7}}
*{{cite book |author=Kate Fox |title=The Flirting Report |url=http://www.sirc.org/publik/advanced_flirting.shtml |publisher=The Social Issues Research Center |year=2004}}
*{{cite book |author=Kate Fox |title=[[Watching the English: the hidden rules of English behaviour]] |year=2004 |publisher=Hodder & Stoughton |isbn=0-340-81886-7}}<br> In this book, Fox does an anthropological analysis by conducting experiments and uses participant observation to discover the unwritten rules that makes an English person English. She tries to explain the cultural norms of the English, which are seen as peculiar by people who aren't English.<ref>Fox, K. (2008). Watching the English the Hidden Rules of English Behaviour. (pp. 1-2, 10, 17). London, UK: Nicholas Brealey Publishing.</ref>

==Current activities==
Recent topics include social effects of [[alcohol]]<ref>{{cite news |last=Fox |first=Kate |title=Viewpoint: Is the alcohol message all wrong? |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-15265317 |accessdate=11 February 2012|newspaper=BBC News |date=11 October 2011}}</ref> and the purposes of small talk.<ref>{{cite news|last=Langley|first=William|title=Why we always warm to the weather|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/topics/weather/8801186/Why-we-always-warm-to-the-weather.html|accessdate=11 February 2012|newspaper=Telegraph|date=1 October 2011}}</ref> Fox is currently writing a book about that “examine[s] many aspects of 21st-century life and obsessions - including mobile phones, social media, online dating, shopping, celebrity, reality TV, computer games, selfies, etc - from an evolutionary/anthropological perspective.”<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sirc.org/about/kate_fox.html|title=Kate Fox|website=www.sirc.org|access-date=2018-08-11}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
In 2004 Fox married the [[neurosurgeon]] and acclaimed author [[Henry Marsh (neurosurgeon)|Henry Marsh]],<ref name="NewStatesman 03 2014">[http://www.newstatesman.com/lifestyle/2014/03/life-and-death-his-fingertips-watching-brain-surgeon-work New Statesman, March 2014, Life and death at his fingertips: watching a brain surgeon at work. by Erica Wagner]</ref> having been previously married to Peter Kibby (during which time she was credited as Kate Fox Kibby).<ref>http://www.philmellows.com/PhilMellows_Diary_17_10_11.htm</ref>

