=== Anime ===
{{see also|List of Sankarea: Undying Love episodes}}
A 12-episode [[anime]] television series based on the manga was announced in the October 2011 issue of ''Bessatsu Shōnen Magazine'', and aired in Japan between April 5 and June 28, 2012.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-09-05/sankarea-zombie-comedy-manga-gets-tv-anime | title = ''Sankarea'' Zombie Comedy Manga Gets TV Anime | publisher = [[Anime News Network]] | date = 2011-09-05 | accessdate = 2011-09-06}}</ref> Two [[original video animation]] episodes were released with the limited edition of the 6th and 7th volumes of the manga on June 8 and November 9, 2012.<ref name=ann1>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-02-09/sankarea-zombie-comedy-manga-to-bundle-unaired-anime|title=''Sankarea'' Zombie Comedy Manga to Bundle Unaired Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2012-02-09|accessdate=2013-12-25}}</ref> A third OVA episode was released with the 6th Blu-ray Disc and DVD volumes on November 30, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B007QR4MGS|title=さんかれあ 6 [Blu-ray]|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-12-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B007QR4N7Q|title=さんかれあ 6 [DVD]|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=2013-12-25}}</ref> The opening theme is {{nihongo|"Esoragoto"|絵空事|Figment}} by [[Nano Ripe]] and the ending theme is "Above Your Hand" by [[Annabel (Japanese singer)|Annabel]]. The series has been licensed in North America by [[Funimation]], released the series dubbed in English on Blu-ray Disc and DVD on October 1, 2013. It was then discovered that the release contained the edited version, Funimation has since recalled and postponed a release on Blu-ray/DVD with the uncensored material, no news of a proper release date has been announced yet until Funimation announced a March 31, 2015 release for the uncut complete series.<ref>http://www.fandompost.com/2014/12/15/funimation-details-march-2015-anime-dvdbd-release-slate/</ref> Customers who have received the edited version can opt to return their copy for refund or exchange their copy for the unedited version when it is distributed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-07-23/funimation-streams-english-dubbed-sankarea/undying-love-trailer |title=Funimation Streams English-Dubbed ''Sankarea: Undying Love'' Trailer |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |date=2012-07-23 |accessdate=2013-12-25}}</ref> [[MVM Films]] has licensed the series in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-03-07/mvm-announces-sankarea-for-later-in-the-year|title=MVM Announces ''Sankarea'' for Later in the Year|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=2013-03-07|accessdate=2013-12-25}}</ref>

=== Novel ===
A novel adaptation was published by Kodansha under their Kodansha Ranobe Bunko [[imprint (trade name)|imprint]] on July 2, 2012. The novel, titled {{nihongo|''Sankarea: All Night-Rea Long''|さんかれあ　おーる・ないとれあ・ろんぐ}}, was written by Ryō Suzukaze and illustrated by Mitsuru Hattori.<ref name=nat1 /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kc.kodansha.co.jp/product/top.php/1234645054|script-title=ja:さんかれあ　おーる・ないとれあ・ろんぐ|language=Japanese|publisher=[[Kodansha]]|accessdate=2013-12-25}}</ref>

== Reception ==
According to [[Oricon]], the complete third volume compilation of the manga sold 24,363 copies,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-03-16/japanese-comic-ranking-march-7-13 | title = Japanese Comic Ranking, March 7–13 | publisher = [[Anime News Network]] | date = 2011-03-16 | accessdate = 2011-09-06}}</ref> while the fourth volume sold 44,120 copies (making it rank #19 of Japanese manga sales in mid-August 2011).<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-08-17/japanese-comic-ranking-august-8-14 | title = Japanese Comic Ranking, August 8–14 | publisher = [[Anime News Network]] | date = 2011-08-18 | accessdate = 2011-09-06}}</ref>

